Argo CD v2.5 release candidate

Four months after the release of Argo CD v2.4, we’re excited to preview version 2.5 with the first release candidate! 128 contributors (85 of them new) made awesome improvements, including 58 new features. Please take the release candidate for a spin and send us feedback about how you’re using new features or about any bugs you encounter.

Beta Support for Server-Side Apply

The Argo CD Application controller can now sync resources using server-side apply. This helps avoid errors when applying very large resources. It also resolves edge-case issues with inaccurate manifest diffs. This feature introduces brand new diffing logic based on how Kubernetes calculates diffs server-side. It is a beta feature that, once thoroughly validated, will be made the default apply option.

Thank you to Leonardo Almeida from Intuit for contributing this enhancement!

API and CLI Support for ApplicationSets, and Advanced Templating

The Argo CD CLI and API now support get/create/update/delete operations on ApplicationSets. You can enable user access to argocd appset commands with the applicationsets RBAC resource.

$ argocd appset create guestbook-appset.yaml
ApplicationSet 'guestbook' created
$ argocd appset get guestbook
Name:               guestbook
Project:            default
Server:             {{url}}
Namespace:          guestbook
Repo:               https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd.git
Target:             HEAD
Path:               applicationset/examples/list-generator/guestbook/{{cluster}}
SyncPolicy:         <none>CONDITION            STATUS  MESSAGE                                                 LAST TRANSITION
ErrorOccurred        False   Successfully generated parameters for all Applications  2022-09-17 19:34:35 -0400 EDT
ParametersGenerated  True    Successfully generated parameters for all Applications  2022-09-17 19:34:35 -0400 EDT
ResourcesUpToDate    True    ApplicationSet up to date                               2022-09-17 19:34:35 -0400 EDT

Thanks to Ishita Sequeira from Red Hat for the major effort to add this feature!

Advanced templating with the go text template engine is now possible in ApplicationSets. This allows things like setting default fallback parameter values and sanitizing/truncating values to be used in DNS fields. Users will have access to functions from the Sprig library, so the possibilities are expansive.

apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: ApplicationSet
metadata:
  name: cluster-addons
spec:
  goTemplate: true
  generators:
  - git:
      repoURL: https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd.git
      revision: HEAD
      directories:
      - path: applicationset/examples/git-generator-directory/cluster-addons/*
  template:
    metadata:
      name: '{{index (splitList "/" .path.path) 0}}'
    spec:
      project: default
      source:
        repoURL: https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd.git
        targetRevision: HEAD
        path: '{{.path.path}}'
      destination:
        server: https://kubernetes.default.svc
        namespace: '{{normalize .path.basename}}'

Thanks to Geoffrey Muselli from Ubisoft for contributing this feature!

Security Improvements

New Project-Level Restrictions

Project destination patterns now support a ! prefix to negate the pattern. This allows blocking deployments to sensitive destinations (for example, the argocd namespace).

There is also a new field to restrict deployments to only project-scoped clusters (the default is to allow deployment to any cluster matching a destination pattern).

Thanks to Blake Pettersson for both of these improvements!

Better Network Security

Traffic between the Argo CD server and the bundled Dex instance is now encrypted by default. And the NetworkPolicy ingress and egress rules between several Argo CD components are now further-restricted, decreasing the risk of lateral movement by an attacker. Thanks to Jake J from Cobalt and to 34fathombelow for these improvements. These folks have put in a lot of work on Argo CD security for this release.

User Interface Improvements

Argo CD supports UI extensions to add custom features to your Argo CD UI. Alexander Matyushentsev from Akuity has added support for loading extensions in the Application details page (instead of just resource pages, like Pods). He has also added support for loading multiple extensions per resource group/kind.

Another enhancement adds the ability to edit HTTPS repository credentials in the Argo CD UI’s “Repositories” page. Previously, the credentials could only be edited by directly modifying a Secret resource in Kubernetes.

Thanks to Yi Cai from Red Hat for contributing this UI enhancement!

Other Notable Changes

  • Add an experimental option to allow applications in any namespace and restrict projects to applications in certain namespaces (by Jann Fischer from Red Hat)
  • The ApplicationSet SCM Provider generator now supports Azure DevOps (by brinchm)
  • The UI now respects the “default container” annotation when displaying logs (by Edward Grönroos)
  • The Argo CD API now supports managing notifications (by Aborilov Pavel from Akuity)
  • Argo CD now supports Gzip-compressing data stored in Redis for lighter network activity (by Alexander Matyushentsev from Akuity)

Where Can I Get the New Release?

For more details and installation instructions, check the release notes, and upgrade instructions. Please try the release candidate and share your feedback. A big thanks to all Argo Community contributors and users for their contributions, feedback, and help in testing the release!

Thanks to Leonardo Luz
